This article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence during a ceremony at the White House to honor law enforcement officers who responded to a shooting incident at a baseball diamond in Alexandria. The Vice President expressed gratitude to the first responders and praised their heroism. He also mentioned that Congressman Steve Scalise, who was injured in the shooting, has been released from the hospital. Pence introduced and applauded the five officers who were present at the ceremony and commended them for their bravery. He concluded by asking the audience to show their appreciation for these officers and all law enforcement personnel.